  "duration": 123.774433792,
  "text": " What exactly is adaptive case management? A GPS system that doesn't react to unexpected traffic jams or road closures? That doesn't allow you to enter stops along the way or get alternative routes? It's unthinkable nowadays. Dynamic traffic management, or adaptive vehicle route management, have been standard features in practically every car for years now. Traffic jams in the office are normal nowadays. Knowledge workers can only dream of adaptive route management. Processes get held up or never reach their destination. The rigid structure is the real problem. Alternative routes were simply never planned in. While this structure may work to a certain extent for invoice verification and approval processes, it doesn't work elsewhere. In many business processes knowledge workers have to make dynamic and situation decisions A normal business process management system reaches its limits pretty quickly for example in handling complaints or claims. The answer to the problem? Adaptive case management. Adaptive case management focuses on the decision-making process and the target, not on the rigidly defined paths to the target. If there's gridlock or a faster route for a process step, then the knowledge worker can look at the situation, break out of the rigid process, and reach the destination faster and more efficiently. DOCSIS 4 supports knowledge-based work processes and provides employees the most relevant information about the case and process step from the very beginning. This means that knowledge workers have constant control over every part of the process, which also helps them to make sound decisions in accordance with regulations. Want to learn more? check out scr-solutions.com slash acm",
